  "texts": [
    "Specifically, IC3Net [48] enables communication between learning agents and their opponents.",
    "Experiments indicate that these opponents eventually learn to not communicate to avoid being exploited.",
    "Some works assume explicit role assignments, i.e., senders and receivers.",
    "The role of the receiver can be taken by a disjoint set of agents separate from the senders [61][62][63] or by all other agents in the environment [60,64].",
    "In both cases, agents communicate with each other directly."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Specifically, IC3Net [48] enables communication between learning agents and their opponents.",
    "The role of the receiver can be taken by a disjoint set of agents separate from the senders [61][62][63] or by all other agents in the environment [60,64]."
  ]
}